headline: Intercontinental Exchange CFO Warren Gardiner to Present at the UBS Financial Services Conference on February 9
summary: ATLANTA and MIAMI, January 26, 2026--Intercontinental Exchange, Inc. (NYSE:ICE), a leading global provider of technology and data, announced today that Warren Gardiner, CFO, will present at the UBS Financial Services Conference. The presentation will take place on Monday, February 9 at 11:20 a.m. ET. The presentation will be available live and in replay via webcast and can be accessed in the investor relations and media section of ICE’s website at http://ir.theice.com.

headline: Live Feed: First Lady Melania Trump Rings NYSE Opening Bell to Celebrate Amazon MGM Studios' Upcoming Film, MELANIA
summary: On Wednesday, January 28th, First Lady Melania Trump will ring The Opening Bell® to celebrate Amazon MGM Studios' global theatrical release on January 30th of MELANIA, a new film that offers unprecedented access to the 20 days leading up to the 2025 Presidential Inauguration through the eyes of the First Lady herself.

headline: NYSE Content Advisory: Pre-Market update + ICE Data Projects Coldest Stretch for U.S. in Decades
summary: The New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) provides a daily pre-market update directly from the NYSE Trading Floor. Access today's NYSE Pre-market update for market insights before trading begins.

headline: ICE First Look at Mortgage Performance: Increased Refinance Activity Drives Mortgage Prepayments Back Toward 3.5-Year High
summary: ATLANTA & NEW YORK, January 26, 2026--ICE Mortgage Technology, neutral provider of a robust end-to-end mortgage platform and part of Intercontinental Exchange, Inc. (NYSE: ICE), today released the December 2025 ICE First Look at mortgage delinquency, foreclosure and prepayment trends.

headline: Intercontinental Exchange (ICE): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q3 Earnings?
summary: Over the last six months, Intercontinental Exchange’s shares have sunk to $173.00, producing a disappointing 5.4% loss - a stark contrast to the S&P 500’s 8.2% gain. This may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
